Rating: 3
The first time I made this salad I thought the bacon dressing was far too greasy. Because the other reviews were so positive, the second time I microwaved the bacon first, saved some of the bacon fat to saute the onions, and then continued with the printed directions. For us, this was much better.

Rating: 4
Delicious. A surprisingly great blend of flavors- if you're wondering if it's going to be as good as the reviews, it is. For a summer version, I would suggest raw onion, draining the grapefruit and cooking the bacon in the microwave (cheating), so everything stays a bit more crisp. I'll make it again!

Rating: 4
Great salad! I followed other reviewers' advice and mixed spinach with bacon mixture and half the dressing before topping with grapefruit and more dressing. I had a ripe avocado on hand so I added that along with the grapefruit. My boyfriend and I ate the whole thing in one very happy night. Will definitely make again and again.

Rating: 3
I made this for a wedding shower in June and enjoyed the different flavors. I didn't saute the onion and prepared the bacon in the oven instead. The bacon looks a lot nicer and is less greasy prepared in the oven and I didn't saute the onions because it would made the salad heavy for an afternoon buffet. The dressing is great and I've made it again by itself. Over all - the salad got rave reviews from a variety of women. Definitely a great salad to make for larger groups.

