Rating: 4
Everyone in my family loved this salad. The sesame seeds add flavor and crunch. I tossed the spinach with about half the dressing and the bacon mixture, plated it, then added the grapefruit on top to avoid breaking up the sections, followed by another drizzle of dressing. Top notch!

Rating: 4
Wonderful and refreshing salad! How did I miss this recipe for so long? I used Texas Ruby Red's, as they are sweeter than white grapefruit. The dressing is exquisite! One word of advice...don't toss the grapefruit with the salad, just add it on top of the greens and add additional dressing. The segments can tend to break up when tossing. I'm a Personal/Private Chef and served this at a formal dinner party. It was a huge hit!

